<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1528,2034]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">
The 
<typeStatus box="[204,254,1528,1554]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">type</typeStatus>
series was from 
<collectingCountry box="[454,524,1528,1554]" name="China" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">China</collectingCountry>
(Guangzhou, Guangdong and Guangxi). In the original description the costal index of the female was given as 
<number box="[550,604,1568,1594]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" value="0.36">0.36</number>
, and this was repeated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Liu" box="[919,1050,1568,1594]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" refString="Liu, G. (2001) A Taxonomic Study of Chinese Phorid Flies Diptera: Phoridae (part 1). China: Neupress. 292 pp." type="book" year="2001">
Liu (
<number box="[977,1041,1568,1594]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" value="2001.0">2001</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. However, this is clearly at odds with his figure of the wing in the latter publication and the costal index of a 
<typeStatus box="[1035,1136,1608,1634]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">paratype</typeStatus>
(see below) is 
<number box="[1311,1433,1608,1634]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" value="0.565" valueMax="0.57" valueMin="0.56">0.56–0.57</number>
. The specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[390,462,1648,1674]" name="South Korea" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">Korea</collectingCountry>
is a little paler than the females from 
<collectingCountry box="[920,990,1648,1674]" name="China" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">China</collectingCountry>
and the costal index is 
<number box="[1273,1394,1648,1674]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" value="0.525" valueMax="0.53" valueMin="0.52">0.52–0.53</number>
. Its abdominal tergites 
<number box="[377,420,1688,1714]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" value="4.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.0">3–6</number>
are as 
<figureCitation box="[505,637,1688,1714]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 26" captionStartId="11.[151,269,1731,1755]" captionTargetBox="[238,1378,221,1684]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[191,1396,197,1705]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 26. Metopina sagittata female, details of abdominal tergites: (23) dorsal view of abdomen from T 2 onwards (After Liu, 2001); (24) T 6; (25) T 3; (26) T 4 and T 5. Scale bar (for 24 – 26) = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184970/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">
Figs 
<number box="[564,637,1688,1714]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" value="25.0" valueMax="26.0" valueMin="24.0">24–26</number>
</figureCitation>
compared with Liu’s figure (
<figureCitation box="[985,1074,1688,1714]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 26" captionStartId="11.[151,269,1731,1755]" captionTargetBox="[238,1378,221,1684]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[191,1396,197,1705]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 26. Metopina sagittata female, details of abdominal tergites: (23) dorsal view of abdomen from T 2 onwards (After Liu, 2001); (24) T 6; (25) T 3; (26) T 4 and T 5. Scale bar (for 24 – 26) = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184970/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">
Fig. 
<number box="[1041,1074,1688,1714]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
). From his figure the length to breadth ratios of T 
<number box="[369,382,1728,1754]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" value="3.0">3</number>
and T 
<number box="[457,472,1728,1754]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" value="4.0">4</number>
are 
<number box="[521,558,1728,1754]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" value="1.5">1.5</number>
: 
<number box="[580,595,1728,1754]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" value="1.0">1</number>
and 
<number box="[652,689,1728,1754]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" value="0.9">0.9</number>
: 
<number box="[711,727,1728,1754]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" value="1.0">1</number>
. For the Korean specimen these ratios are 
<number box="[1225,1261,1728,1754]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" value="1.1">1.1</number>
: 
<number box="[1284,1299,1728,1754]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" value="1.0">1</number>
and 
<number box="[1355,1392,1728,1754]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" value="0.9">0.9</number>
: 
<number box="[1414,1430,1728,1754]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" value="1.0">1</number>
. However, the difference for T 
<number box="[510,523,1768,1794]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" value="3.0">3</number>
is probably not significant as the front margin of the tergite is not only less well defined than the other margins but is frequently partly obscured by partial overlap by the posterior edge of segment 
<number box="[292,310,1848,1874]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" value="2.0">2</number>
. Also there is evidently some variation as Liu gives the wing length as 
<number box="[1175,1227,1848,1874]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" value="0.94">0.94</number>
–1.0 mm. For the Korean specimen the length is 
<quantity box="[513,620,1888,1914]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="1.1">1.10 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
